property.name: name
property.value: Third Stratum

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Welcome to our village, haiku! Our chief is waiting for you at the top of the tree. You can use the trampolines here to climb up to him.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: It's is a human! We haven't seen a human here for many years, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Sorry, my momma told me not to talk to strangers, haiku.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Hi, human! What do you think of our village? It's a little different than the towns you're used to, right haiku?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Do you like the trampolines? I built them myself, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Have you met all four types of spirits yet, haiku? There's wood, sun, water, and leaf, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: What type of spirit are you? I've never seen one that looks so fleshy... You're kind of creepy, haiku.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Human! I have important information to tell you, haiku! In this village we use trilobites as currency instead of gold. You can find them by mining fossil rocks in the caves to the west! Was I helpful, haiku?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: As spirits, it's our role to help regulate the natural life on this mountain. I hear you've been helping us by donating to our shrines. Thank you, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Hm? How do we avoid burning down our homes? What a silly question, haiku! This tree, and the wood we make our homes out of, is made of petrified wood. Petrified wood doesn't burn, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Hi human! Have you explored the volcano to the east yet? It's hot, so it's perfect for us sun spirits, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: This is one of our storerooms. If you don't have business here, please leave. I'm very busy, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Daddy is always too busy to play with me... I'm sad, haiku...

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Welcome to Cafe Spirit, human! Unfortunately, spirit food is invisible to humans... but our patrons are hungry for some different cuisine, so if you brought any human food maybe you could sell it to them for trilobites! Yes, that's a great idea! Just ask the customers what flavors they'd like, and give them food that you think fits their request! Give it a try, haiku! Oh, and you can sell to the spirits sitting at our overflow seating uptrampoline, too!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Hi human! This is overflow seating for Cafe Spirit. If you haven't already, please go talk to my boss downtrampoline.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Spin the Wheel of Fate, haiku! Only 10 trilobites, paid directly to the wheel! May fortune be in your favor, human!

properties.property:
Get off my lawn! Darn whippersnappers...
Did I do a good job, haiku? I'm a human enthusiast, so I built my home to emulate human architecture perfectly!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Hi human!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Oh, I'm not hungry right now, haiku. But have you tried jumping on that trampoline to the right? Take a rolling start and it'll send you flying, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: How did you get here, haiku? This is an exclusive club for wood spirits! No sun, water, or leaf spirits allowed!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Mom and Dad won't let me go swimming, haiku...

property.name: dialogue
property.value: What is it, human? Don't you have other humans to be bothering?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: A wooden hammock by the lava... surrounded by coconut trees... I think I'm in heaven, haiku.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: There's an entrance to the volcano up here, haiku. Be careful not to hurt yourself on the way up!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Human! We built a campsite for you over here! I hope you enjoy it, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: The pool of water at the base of our tree is the birthing place of all spirits. It's a sacred place, so please treat it with respect, haiku.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Aren't the trampolines fun, haiku?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Can you keep a secret, human? The leaf spirit hideout is just to the west of here, underground. Don't tell any of the other spirits that I told you, ok haiku?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: I'm keeping guard over the leaf spirit hideout. The rules just say to keep out the sun, water, and wood spirits, so I guess you can go down.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: This is the best place in the whole world, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Have you tried the trampoline tunnels yet, haiku? You might need to roll up into a ball to fit, haiku.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: All four spirits have a special hideout near the tree, haiku. Have you found them all?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Do you like pineapples on your pizza, haiku?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: This garden is perfect for picnics, right haiku?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: No fair, why do I always have to be the spirit, haiku?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: We're playing "Humans & Spirits". I get to be the human this time!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: We wood spirits live in neighborhoods like these. I'm not sure where the other types of spirit live, haiku.|Have you met the archaeologist who lives to the far northwest? I don't think I could ever live so far from home, haiku.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Hey human! Try jumping off to the left of this branch! I think you'll find something cool over there, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Did you fall down here, haiku? Try rolling onto the trampolines from the right, there's something cool to the left.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: I like playing in the sand! Have you seen the castles I built down below, haiku?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: How did you get so big, human? Someday I want to be big and strong like you, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Is it true that all human houses are built differently, haiku? Isn't that a hassle?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Marketplace to the right! We don't accept credit, only trilobites!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: It's my job to water the bean farms every day. It's easy for a water spirit like me, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Do you like to swim too, human? You might enjoy the lava pools, though they are a bit chilly.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Horray! I love burning things, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Are you feeling ok, human? Your face is starting to look a bit red, haiku.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: I can't believe I got stuck guarding the volcano entrance AGAIN, haiku! It's so HOT! Go ahead if you want, I don't care anymore.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Have you come for a quick dip too, human?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: How do we wear towels without them burning off? Well... that's a great question, haiku.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Do you think the volcano is going to erupt again soon? I missed my chance to ride the lava up through the tunnels last week, haiku.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: I want to get closer to the lava... but I'm afraid of heights... help, haiku...

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Human! I built the most AWESOME trampoline ever! Give it a try, haiku! It'll send you FLYING!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: How did you find our hideout, haiku? Well, just stay away from the secret chest at the bottom of the lake and nobody has to get hurt.

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Do you like to fish, haiku? There's different types of fish in this pond than in other ponds lower on the mountain. And of course there's different fish in the lava pools, too!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: These leaf spirits are such suckers. They'll stand on a post for an ear of corn a day! I love cheap labour, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Buy from me, haiku! I sell only the finest crops in all the village!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Best prices, haiku! You won't find nicer fish for this cheap anywhere! I might as well be putting myself out of business with these discounts!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Welcome to Sunny & Sun's Ore Emp-ore-ium, haiku!

property.name: dialogue
property.value: I wish my husband gave the same amount of attention to me as he does to his trampolines, haiku...

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Hi human! I'm an archaeologist studying the past of this region. If you have any rare fossils, I'll trade you Trilobites for them! Oh, and I'll also take fossil shards off your hands for trilobites, maybe at a 5-to-1 ratio, haiku?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: My dad makes trampolines! Isn't that awesome, haiku?

property.name: dialogue
property.value: Hi, haiku! I'm working on developing this area. Do you think a nail spa would work well here?
